{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"74acff2a-7579-4369-b2cd-5f65ab7eed5e","content":"**MSTest.Sdk 4.x dropped the VSTest compatibility bridge by default.**\n\nIn 3.x, even when using Microsoft Testing Platform, the VSTest adapter/bridge was still included so `vstest.console` could discover tests. In 4.x, only the native Microsoft Testing Platform runner ships — `vstest.console` sees zero tests because there's no VSTest adapter present.\n\n**You have two options:**\n\n1. **Re-enable the bridge** — add this to your `.csproj`:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TestingPlatformEnableVSTestBridge>true</TestingPlatformEnableVSTestBridge>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n2. **Switch your CI to the native runner** (recommended) — replace `vstest.console` with:\n   ```bash\n   dotnet test          # or run the test exe directly\n   ```\n\n   `dotnet test` in recent .NET SDK versions supports Microsoft Testing Platform natively, so no bridge is needed.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"0de15f02-d641-4922-bcd6-83a80b8db69a","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about a breaking change when upgrading from MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0 to MSTest.Sdk/4.1.0, specifically about test discovery with vstest.console. This is a knowledge question about MSTest SDK changes, not a code task. Let me answer based on what I know.\n\nStarting with MSTest.Sdk 3.4+, the default test runner changed from VSTest to Microsoft Testing Platform (MTP). But actually, let me think more carefully.\n\nMSTest.Sdk 3.x included both VSTest and Microsoft Testing Platform support by default. The key change is:\n\n- In MSTest.Sdk 3.x, `EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatform` defaulted to `false` (VSTest was the default runner)\n\n\n- Starting with MSTest.Sdk 4.0, `EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatform` defaults to `true`, and the VSTest adapter is no longer included by default, which is why vstest.console can't discover tests anymore.\n\nThe solution is to either switch to `dotnet test` or the test executable directly, disable the Microsoft Testing Platform to revert to VSTest, or explicitly add the VSTest bridge back to the project.","outputTokens":822,"requestId":"0BC0:29D6CF:B3375D:CFC34C:69F024B4"},"id":"7adea681-7e88-46d6-b800-52d48d8924fa","timestamp":"2026-04-28T03:08:54.003Z","parentId":"58eed0e4-ae6a-46b5-a3cc-a07819ca4eaf"}
